Project: Investigate a Dataset - [No-show Appointment]¶

Table of Contents¶

  • Introduction
  • Data Wrangling
  • Exploratory Data Analysis
  • Conclusions

Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

In this project, we will analyse the dataset of No-show appointments. It is composed of 14 variables described as follow\ 01 - PatientId: Identification of a patient\ 02 - AppointmentID: Identification of each appointment\ 03 - Gender: Male or Female\ 04 - Scheduled Day: The day of the actual appointment, when they have to visit the doctor.\ 05 - Appointment Day: The day someone called or registered the appointment.\ 06 - Age\ 07 - Neighbourhood: Where the appointment takes place.\ 08 - Scholarship: If the patient is enrolled in Brasilian welfare program to provide financial aid to poor Brazilian families. \ 09 - Hipertension\ 10 - Diabetes\ 11 - Alcoholism\ 12 - Handcap\ 13 - SMS_received: As a reminder of the appointment\ 14 - No-show: If the patient did show up to their appointment or not. No if the patient showed up to their appointment, and Yes if they did not show up.

Questions for Analysis¶

01 - Is there a relationship between a patient's age and no-show?\ 02 - Is there a relationship between a patient's gender and no-show?\ 03 - Does the Scheduled Day affect the No-show decision?

Exploratory Data Analysis¶

For this Dataset No_show is the dependent variable and Age, Gender and Scheduled Day are the independent variables

We will define a function to plot the independent variable x with a bar plot.

In [98]:
def figure(x):
    Conc= df.groupby([x]).No_show.value_counts()
    fig = Conc.plot(kind='bar', figsize= (10,5),color =['#66CDAA','#708090'], alpha = 0.7, width = 0.5);
    plt.title("No_show/show" )
    plt.xlabel(x)
    plt.ylabel('variable Count')
    plt.show()
    return fig

For that, we will define a function Pie(X) to plot the percentages.

In [108]:
def Pie(x):
    fig = px.pie(x,names='Ages_category',values = 'No_show', color_discrete_sequence=px.colors.sequential.Darkmint,
             width=500, height=300)
    return fig

Conclusions¶

For this project, we analysed a dataset of patients appointments from 110521 patients ID to analyse whether or not the patients show up for their appointment.\ 79,8 % of the patients did show up for their appointment whereas 20,2 % did not show up.\

01 - Is there a relationship between a patient's age and no-show?\ We categorized the ages data to categories:\ Seniors 27499 Young Adults 27250 Middle Aged Adults 26906 Child Adolescence 25327 We conclude that, according to the age category that patients that belongs to the Seniors are more likely to show up for their appointment with a percentage of 27,2%. While, patients that belong to the Young Adults category are less likely to show up with a percentage of 29,6%. Therefor, age is an important factor to determine if a patient will show up or not.

02 - Is there a relationship between a patient's gender and no-show?\ There are 71834 Females and 38687 Males in this dataset. We used proportions to have a clearer idea.\ We conclude that, Females and Males have almost the same probabily of whether showing up or not.Therefor, Gender is not an important factor to decide if a patient will show up or not.

03 - Does the Scheduled Day affect the No-show decision?\ We used the day of the week to determine if the patients will show up or not for their appointment.\ Tuesday is the day with the highest number of showing up 20875. Whereas, on Saturday there were only 24 scheduled appointments. As for Sunday, we assumed that the medical centers do not work.\ We conclude that, the scheduled day is an important factor to determine if a patient will show up or not.\

Limitations:\ From the dataset, we can see that the period range is 6 months, may be If we have a dataset for a longer time, for a year for instance, we could have a better and clearer idea. Another factor that would be important and helpful is to know the patient's adress to see if he is close to the Neighbourhood or not. I think the distance is an important factor. \ From the above analysis, we could see that Age,Gender and the scheduled day are some of the factors that would help us determine if the patient will Show up for the appointment or not.
